/cli

# === Security reports (never commit scanner output) ===
reports/security/
reports/security-cache/
# === END Security reports ===

# === Secret hygiene (CONST-041) — added P0-06 ===
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# .env.full-test is mock-only test fixtures (every API key is `mock-*-for-testing`,
# passwords are `*_test_password`; no real secrets — not a CONST-042 leak). It is
# sourced from disk by the Makefile (`. ./.env.full-test` in test-full/test-*-full
# targets) and is NOT generated by scripts/setup-full-test-env.sh, so a fresh clone
# requires it tracked. Explicit negation keeps the ignore-line and tracked-state
# consistent (CONST-053 repository-hygiene).
!.env.full-test
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.pub
helix.security.json
# === END Secret hygiene ===

# Worktrees created by HelixCode P1-F04 EnterWorktree (do NOT commit)
.helix-worktrees/

